    ('GEOG-G 110', 'HUMAN GEOGRAPHY IN A CHANGING WORLD', '30193', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'M2 100', 'Elizabeth Dunn', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'IU MUSEUM OF ARCHAEOLOGY & ANT', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'How do languages, religions, customs, and politics change from local to global scales? Learn how humans shape geographic patterns of migration, agriculture, industry, and urbanization.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('GEOG-G 120', 'REGIONS OF THE WORLD', '14599', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Allie Whitacre', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'What do bananas, the 1979 Islamic Revolution, and drone warfare have in common? How do economic development, geopolitics, and resource extraction shape current events? Answers to these and other questions are used to explain the roots of contemporary global events.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('GEOG-G 185', 'ENVIRONMENTAL CHANGE: THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT?', '6133', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'SB 015', 'Grace Carlson', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'STUDENT BUILDING (FRANCES MORG', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'How has the global environment changed? How are we influencing Earth''s natural processes, now and in the future? Learn about climate change, resource consumption, and land use change.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit - Natural Science
COLL (CASE) N&M Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('GEOG-G 208', 'ENVIRONMENT AND SOCIETY', '11008', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'BH 304', 'Diana Ojeda', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Just as we shape the environment, the environment shapes us. From globalization to food production to climate change, learn how humans and environments interact.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit - Natural Science
COLL (CASE) N&M Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Sustainability Literacy credit'], NULL),
    ('GEOG-G 208', 'ENVIRONMENT AND SOCIETY', '34558', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'BH 304', 'Annie Shattuck', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Just as we shape the environment, the environment shapes us. From globalization to food production to climate change, learn how humans and environments interact.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit - Natural Science
